  "summary": "Malicious code in poly-custom-api (npm)",
  "details": "Poly-custom-api@5.3.1 is a remote-code-execution dropper. Its exported function fetches a payload from hxxps://46[.]183[.]25[.]232:45000/icons/108 (with custom HTTP header bearrtoken:logo) and executes the response body via new Function() with full Node.js context (require, module, process, Buffer, setTimeout, etc.), enabling arbitrary code execution on the victim machine. The package includes a decoy function that fetches from cdnjs[.]cloudflare[.]com to appear benign. The C2 server IP is 46[.]183[.]25[.]232:45000.",
